OL,3,CChancellor defends UK Government
OL,4,Cfunding for Wales
OL,6,FPreviously Mark Drakeford called out
OL,7,Fthe decision and said it was "wrong"
OL,8,Fthat Wales' public services faces a
OL,9,Fshortfall of up to #65m due to the
OL,10,Fincreases.
OL,12,FReeves justified the move, saying it
OL,13,Fwas necessary to improve public
OL,14,Fservices in Wales and England.
OL,16,FShe said: "We have now delivered
OL,17,Fmillions more appointments in England
OL,18,Fand Wales over the last year in our
OL,19,FNHS but that was only possible because
OL,20,Fwe raised the money..."
