OL,3,CChancellor defends UK Government
OL,4,Cfunding for Wales
OL,6,F"I do recognise the challenges raises
OL,7,Fin National Insurance creates but
OL,8,Fwithout that money we would not be
OL,9,Fable to secure our public finances."
OL,11,FPlaid Cymru MS Heledd Fychan described
OL,12,FRachel Reeves as "out of touch",
OL,13,Fciting a rise in unemployment due to
OL,14,FNational Insurance contributions.
OL,16,FShe said: "Rachel Reeves' decisions
OL,17,Fhave directly harmed Wales... if you
OL,18,Fasked anyone in Wales if they think
OL,19,FRachel Reeves is doing a good job, I
OL,20,Fthink it would be a resounding no"
